JD-4
LINK- https://in.indeed.com/q-sound-engineer-jobs.html?vjk=8d185b875b1d36bf
As a Sound Engineer specializing in music and sound design for slot games, you will be responsible for curating, editing, and integrating high-quality sounds and music into our games to create immersive and engaging auditory experiences.

As a Sound Engineer/ Artist, your main responsibility will be to understand all game themes and design sounds and music to create a very immersive user experience and create suitable mocks for developers to understand and implement accordingly.

Your responsibilities will include:

1. Sound Selection: Identify and select appropriate sounds, music tracks, and audio effects to complement the theme and game play of our games and marketing assets.

2. Sound Editing and Mixing: Edit and manipulate audio files to ensure clarity, balance, and cohesion within the game environment. Mix multiple audio elements to achieve desired levels. Using Adobe premiere or other tools to edit and create music.

3. Quality Assurance: Conduct thorough testing and debugging of audio assets to identify and resolve any issues related to playback, synchronization, or performance.

4. Collaboration: Work closely with game designers, artists, animators and developers to align audio elements with the overall creative vision and Slot gameplay mechanics.

Mandatory Skills Requirements

1. Bachelor's degree in Audio Engineering, Music Production, or a related field or equivalent professional experience.

2. Proven experience in sound design, music composition, and audio editing within the gaming industry, with a focus on slot games preferred.

3. Strong understanding of sound design principles.

