Job Description:

We are hiring for Sound/Audio Engineer for Deluxe Entertainment.

Requirements:

B.Sc. degree in computer science, electronics, or A/V technology related field, or Diploma in Audio Engineering.
Minimum 1 year of experience in audio editing.
Excellent working knowledge of Avid or Digi Design Protools HD.
Strong technical understanding of digital audio, including sample rates, bit rates, audio speed, digital audio sync, SMPTE time code, video sync, and video codecs.
Strong understanding and experience with all common audio configurations, including 7.1, 5.1, 2.0, and Mono.
Excellent operational skills of Apple macOS.
Good communication skills.
Responsibilities:

Perform audio editing, frame rate conversions, and audio conforms on stereo/5.1 audio files for perfect sync.
Have a good understanding of various video frame rates.
Efficiently use audio interfaces, audio monitoring equipment, and digital audio workstations to produce high-quality audio files.
Identify various audio anomalies and attempt to fix them in-house or report them back to the client.
Ensure tasks are completed in a timely manner and update work trackers on a daily basis.
Responsible for maintaining audio equipment and ensuring good functionality without any malfunctions or downtime.
