Full job description
Assisting senior sound engineers in setting up and operating audio equipment for recording, mixing, and mastering audio tracks.
Learning how to use various audio software and hardware, including digital audio workstations , mixing consoles, microphones, amplifiers, and signal processors.
Participating in studio and on-location recording sessions, including setting up microphones, positioning equipment, and troubleshooting technical issues.
Assisting with sound checks and adjusting audio levels during live events, performances, or recordings.
Cleaning and maintaining audio equipment to ensure optimal performance and longevity.
Collaborating with other members of the production team, such as musicians, producers, directors, and sound designers, to achieve desired audio outcomes.
Following safety procedures and guidelines to prevent accidents and ensure a safe working environment.
Continuously learning and staying updated on advancements in audio technology and techniques.

